description: This layer is the Ozark-St. Francis National Forest trails layer. A trail is defined as a route 50 inches or less in width or a route over 50 inches wide that is identified and managed as a trail (36 CFR 212.1). Including hiking, motorized, non-motorized, equestrian and aquatic.
